 Faculty profile 

 
 

  Hal  Stern</strong>  Professor</strong>  DEGREE: Ph.D., 1987 Stanford University  RESEARCH AREAS:  Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning Statistics and Statistical Theory  RESEARCH INTERESTS:  Prof. Stern's research interests include: statistical inference using Bayesian methods, assessing the fit of statistical models, applications of statistics in the social and biological sciences, and statistics in sports. He has authored more than 50 publications (more than 30 refereed publications), and is a co-author of the graduate level statistics text "Bayesian Data Analysis".  CONTACT INFORMATION:            
                    
                        E-mail:</strong> 
                        sternh(at)uci(period)edu  
                        Office:</strong> 
                       DBH 2216 
                        Phone:</strong> 
                       (949) 824-1568 
                        Fax:</strong> 
                       (949) 824-9863 
                        Website:</strong> 
                        www.ics.uci.edu/~sternh/  
                       
 
 
